In the second of the finals, he was [[Man of the Match]] for the third consecutive game, top&amp;ndash;scoring for England with 70 and taking two wickets, as well another difficult catch off the bowling of [[Sajid Mahmood]] to once again dismiss [[Matthew Hayden]].&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite web
